docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:1:# 0015 — The ceiling is the session model, not a config value
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-2-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-3-- **Status:** active — owner-approved 2026-07-09; **built in 0.1.14** (2026-07-09). Refines decision 0012. Lib suite green (64/64), onboarding suite green.
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-4-- **Date:** 2026-07-09
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:5:- **Source:** owner, reviewing the 0012 `models` config: *"ceiling không cần config, nó nên luôn luôn lấy model hiện tại đang được chọn để chạy; chỉ có generation, extraction là cho chọn model."* The ceiling tier being a configured value was both redundant and slightly wrong — the ceiling **is** the orchestrator's own model by definition, so naming it separately invites drift (config says `fable` while the session runs on `opus`).
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-6-- **Confidence:** 0.8 (clean simplification; the only wrinkle is advisor mode, handled below).
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-7-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-8-## Decision
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-9-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:10:**The ceiling tier is never configured. It is always the model running the session** (the orchestrator's own model). Config `models` holds only the two cheaper tiers you downgrade workers to:
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-11-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-12-```json
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-13-"models": {
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:14:  "claude": { "extraction": "haiku", "generation": "sonnet" },
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:15:  "codex":  { "extraction": null, "generation": null }
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-16-}
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-17-```
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-18-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:19:- `modelForTier(root, 'ceiling', …)` returns **null** = "inherit the session model" → swarming omits the Agent `model` param, so a ceiling cell runs on whatever the session runs on.
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:20:- `CONFIGURABLE_TIERS = ['extraction', 'generation']`; `normalizeModels` reads only those, and a stray `ceiling` key in a config file is ignored.
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:21:- `MODEL_TIERS` still lists `ceiling` — cells can be **tiered** ceiling ("keep this on the session model, don't downgrade"), and the scarcity warning still counts them.
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-22-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-23-## Advisor mode gets its own named model
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-24-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:25:Advisor mode (decision 0013) is the one case where the strong model is **not** the session model — there the session runs on the cheap `generation` tier and phones a stronger expert. So the advisor names its model explicitly:
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-26-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-27-```json
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-28-"advisor": { "enabled": true, "at": ["shape", "execution", "blocked"], "model": "fable" }
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-29-```
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-30-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:31:`advisorModel(root, point)` returns `config.advisor.model` (default `fable`) — it no longer borrows the ceiling tier (which, under 0015, would be the cheap session and defeat the purpose).
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-32-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-33-## Rationale
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-34-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:35:- **Truthful by construction.** The ceiling can't drift from the session model because it *is* the session model — there is nothing to keep in sync.
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:36:- **Less to configure.** The common setup ("run on my best model, send workers cheaper") needs only `generation`/`extraction`. The user picks the ceiling by choosing what to run the session on — which they already do.
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:37:- **The two patterns stay clean.** Fan-out: session = strong, ceiling inherits it. Advisor: session = cheap, `advisor.model` = the strong expert. Each names exactly what it must.
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-38-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-39-## Alternatives considered
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-40-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:41:- **Keep ceiling in `models` (0012 as-is).** Rejected per the owner — redundant and drift-prone.
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md:42:- **Let advisor reuse `models.*.ceiling`.** No longer possible (ceiling isn't configured); and conceptually wrong, since advisor's expert is stronger than the session, not the session.
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-43-
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-44-## Scope (built)
docs/decisions/0015-ceiling-is-the-session-model.md-45-
